snippet.title: üî¥FIT FRESH AND FANTASTIC EPISODE 1 LIVE WITH AMBER GOT THE JUICE
snippet.description:

Live Interview show on health wellness fitness and freshness.

Jalik TheLeader on all Social Media

https://ambergotthejuice.com/

Juicing helped to change my life‚Ä¶.literally!  I am excited to share my journey of living a healthier life style with you.  I hope that by sharing my story, I can encourage you to become healthy with the ultimate goal of improving your quality of life. For years I struggled with defining Gods purpose for my life.  I knew that I enjoyed helping people, however I realized that I needed to narrow my focus, so I did a little soul searching to figure out the best way I could serve others.  My answer didn‚Äôt come quick, and needless to say I had no idea that I was about to embark on a journey that would shake me at my core. 

 More about that later‚Ä¶.. 

 

I started juicing and creating smoothie recipes in 2013. Just for fun. I did this almost every day in my kitchen.  After about a year, I slowly got pulled away from my juicing ritual due to increasing demands from my job and a hectic work schedule.  I stopped juicing for almost a year.  I just could never find the time- 

 

In 2015, I starting having joint pains throughout my body, but I thought that it was due to me being tired, and that I just needed to stretch.  I also noticed that I was sleepy ALL THE TIME‚Ä¶even after getting 8 hours of sleep.  My pain increased and became so severe that it hurt for me to walk, sit, get up, flush the toilet, bathe, drive, open doors and get dressed.  Basically‚Ä¶every joint in my body hurt. 

 

After a year of going to several specialist including 3 different Rheumatologist, I finally got my diagnosis‚Ä¶rheumatoid arthritis. As you can imagine, to get this diagnosis at 26 years old, I was devastated.  I couldn‚Äôt understand how and why I developed this disease when there was no known history of it in my family.  

 

I was literally unhappy for months‚Ä¶ but I didn‚Äôt stay there.  It was time to put ME first. I decided that I would fight. 

 

 I was determined to beat this disease, even though I was told that there was not a cure.  I started doing my research, and was amazed to learn about the link between diet and certain diseases. 

Then it suddenly came to me‚Ä¶..JUICING!!! So the BEAST reminded me of the BEAUTY of juicing. 

 

I am excited to report that my health has made a dramatic turnaround since I started back juicing and modifying my diet.   I am well on the way to putting my RA into remission‚ÄîI no longer have joint pain. I am also proud to say that I found a passion‚Ä¶so let me help you discover your ‚Äúhealthier self‚Äù by trying out my delicious juices and smoothies. I am so thankful for all of your support and positive feedback.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Continue Their Red Carpet Grand Slam at The Danish Girl TIFF Premiere
snippet.description:
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp are the definition of Hollywood glamour.

The coupled dazzled on the red carpet for the premiere of The Danish Girl on Saturday at the Toronto International Film Festival. They walked the carpet hand in hand, posing for pictures together along the way.

Heard looked stunning in a glittering gold-and-taupe gown with metallic embellishments. The 29-year-old actress left her hair down and wavy for the occasion and accessorized her look with gold jewelry.

Depp, 52, complemented the earth tones of his wife's dress in a brown pin-stripped suit. Keeping to his signature style, he donned a gray fedora hat, sunglasses and layered pendant necklaces.

snippet.title: Amber Heard, Johnny Depp Are Engaged!
snippet.description:
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp are engaged a year-and-a-half after confirming their relationship in June 2012, a source tells us.
Johnny Depp really did put a ring on it! After Amber Heard was spotted trying to hide some suspiciously flashy bling on her left ring finger earlier this week, fans wondered whether the actress had secretly gotten engaged to her Rum Diary costar. The famously private couple have yet to confirm or deny either way, but sources tell Us Weekly they're indeed planning to marry.
"The proposal happened a while ago," one insider tells Us. "She just didn't wear the ring." (Celebuzz reported news of an engagement on Thursday.)
The 50-year-old Into the Woods actor first met his bride-to-be on the set of their movie The Rum Diary. They confirmed their relationship in June 2012, shortly after Depp announced his split from longtime love Vanessa Paradis, with whom he has two kids, daughter Lily-Rose, 14, and son Jack, 11.
Since then, the typically private duo have been spotted all over the world together, from Moscow to Japan, where they took Depp's kids in July. More recently, on Saturday, Jan. 11, the duo appeared at the Art of Elysium's 7th Annual HEAVEN Gala in L.A., where they held hands and posed for pictures. They also attended the 2014 Golden Globe Awards on Jan. 12.
PHOTOS: Johnny Depp's movie makeovers
Later this year, the couple will reunite onscreen in London Fields, a crime thriller based on the 1989 novel of the same name by Martin Amis. Depp has a cameo on the movie, which also stars Billy Bob Thornton, Jim Sturgess, and Theo James.
